                        <msItem xml:id="MS_Thurston_26-item2" n="2">
                            <title type="desc">A tract on the rites and observances in Islām.</title>
                            <author key="person_f407">anonymous</author>
                            <incipit xml:lang="ota"> هر مكلّف یعنی عاقل و بالغ اولنه اولا لازم و
                                واجب اولدر که الخ ... غازی خضوع و خشوع اوزرینه ادا ايلمك ادا ايلمك
                                اولدر که اذان اوقندوغى وقتن الخ ... الحمد لله ... بوندنصكره معلوم
                                اولا که هر عاقل و بالغ اولان کشیه الخ</incipit>
                            <note>NOTE: This record has been automatically generated with minimal
                                modification from the corresponding entry in a printed catalogue. It
                                may contain errors. Please, consult the References section below for
                                more information.</note>
                            <note>Consisting of three short pieces, the first beginning, on fol. 1b:
                                هر مكلّف یعنی عاقل و بالغ اولنه اولا لازم و واجب اولدر که الخ; the
                                second, on fol. 4b: غازی خضوع و خشوع اوزرینه ادا ايلمك ادا ايلمك
                                اولدر که اذان اوقندوغى وقتن الخ; the third, on fol. 7a: الحمد لله
                                .... بوندنصكره معلوم اولا که هر عاقل و بالغ اولان کشیه الخ. Dated
                                beginning of Ẕī l-ḥicce, A. H. 1088=A. D. 1678, end of
                                January.</note>
                            <listBibl>
                                <bibl><ref
                                        target="https://menadoc.bibliothek.uni-halle.de/publicdomain/content/titleinfo/775134"
                                        >Ethé, Hermann. <title>Catalogue of the Persian, Turkish,
                                            Hindûstânî and Pushtû Manuscripts in the Bodleian
                                            Library, Part II: Turkish, Hindûstânî, Pushtû and
                                            Additional Persian Manuscripts</title>. Oxford:
                                        Clarendon Press. 1930. § (216) 2254.</ref></bibl>
                            </listBibl>
                            <textLang mainLang="ota">Ottoman Turkish</textLang>
                        </msItem>
                        <msItem xml:id="MS_Thurston_26-item3" n="3">
